• Remedial measures

📣 Recap of the week:
‣ We discussed the #FutureofEurope with @EmmanuelMacron
‣ reported on enlargement and #WesternBalkans
‣ unveiled new #SecurityUnion initiatives
‣ presented outcome of #EUTrade negotiations with Japan and Singapore
More → https://t.co/NehEaoqusu https://t.co/ot625myZwm

The #DataProtection clock is ticking!
In few days, our new EU rules will come into application, granting new rights to EU citizens. What does it mean for you?  
Learn more about #GDPR → https://t.co/eUYVho41OG https://t.co/O15Zw07w71

A complaint we heard on Dieselgate was that EU failed to act. In reality, our margin of manoeuvre was limited. We now agreed on reform that gives us power to make sure manufacturers will no longer get away with cheating. We welcome EP green light.  https://t.co/iZ8zkiEsp3 https://t.co/ra55K2X86I

Anti-dumping duties on imports of Chinese steel ropes and cables will continue. 

We are using the full potential of our trade defence toolbox to ensure a level-playing-field for our producers and their ability to maintain jobs in the sector.
https://t.co/ul0FDbmQVf #EUTrade https://t.co/BAV1r3J9Kx

The EU reached a new peak in employment rate!
In 2017, the employment rate of people aged 20 to 64 in the European Union stood at 72.2%, up compared with 2016. The upward trend is visible both for women and men→ https://t.co/ZI6MUTLutf https://t.co/iCTkIJ7ceE

We are looking fror IT experts, coders and bright minds to help us unlock the potential of #blockchain. Join our first-ever anti-counterfeiting blockchain competition in Europe. 
Apply to the #EUBlockathon2018 by 30 April → https://t.co/a1GZmp3ybZ https://t.co/tL7XUU3lyJ

In less than two weeks, we will present our proposals for a #EUBudget beyond 2020. EU Leaders will then have the opportunity to decide on a budget that helps us build the Europe we aspire to. #FutureofEurope https://t.co/WThhYEXytr

We welcome today's adoption of the 5th Anti-Money Laundering Directive by the @Europarl_EN.
These new rules will bring more transparency to fight money laundering and terrorist financing across the EU → https://t.co/DG8AKY5AiQ https://t.co/dgMDdLGUKF

We supported a breakthrough discovery in cancer research.
Researchers @ULBRecherche backed by @ERC_Research have identified the types of tumor cells causing metastases. This will have major implications for the diagnosis and therapy of cancer patients → https://t.co/S0mZhFcAJz https://t.co/0iHZCrxszi

Almost one in ten people in the EU work in retail companies.
We are publishing a set of best practices to create a more open, integrated and competitive retail sector → https://t.co/5EEcB3txNw https://t.co/OdUzW1Zf52

We propose to improve the security features of EU citizens' identity cards with
🔒 common EU security standards
☝ mandatory biometric data
📉 gradual phase out of non-compliant cards
Learn more → https://t.co/sm8ORx11tt  #SecurityUnion https://t.co/oObQobG2GM

Electronic evidence is increasingly important in criminal proceedings. 
We are making sure that criminals and terrorists cannot exploit communication technologies to hide their criminal actions and evade justice → https://t.co/iklxJJ7B3T  #SecurityUnion https://t.co/c2VF2Zt9J2

We stand up for an open, rules-based and fair trade order. 
Today, we presented the outcome of negotiations with like-minded economic partners: Japan and Singapore → https://t.co/dgwxTbupz3 #TradeEU https://t.co/ItxUA2tw97

Are you a company looking for financing to turn your project idea into reality?
Have a look at the #EIPP portal – the EU's online matchmaking platform connecting EU businesses and their projects with investors across the world → https://t.co/iSp8G6dnmi https://t.co/WSWn0v7UNk

Each of us produces nearly a half tonne of municipal waste every year. Together we can turn waste into a valuable resource! 
The @Europarl_EN has just approved our #WasteToResource package
Learn more → https://t.co/ywXfLi22AD #CircularEconomy https://t.co/wnYhAGw6aP
Commissioner @GOettingerEU Statement on the European Parliament's Resolution on Integrity Policy of the European Commission → https://t.co/Ae4GZ0E31r

#FairTaxation is central to the EU social and economic model.
Over the course of 2018, we will organise seminars in Latvia, Austria, France, Ireland and Italy to foster active knowledge exchange to tackle tax abuse and avoidance 
Learn more → https://t.co/VbXle4OuXl https://t.co/1O84HutPjs

The #JunckerPlan is now set to trigger €283.7 billion in investments, representing 90% of the original target. The top five countries benefiting from these growth-focused investments are Greece, Estonia, Bulgaria, Portugal and Spain. 
More → https://t.co/T7hKFvSsaj #investEU https://t.co/zB5yjrbm90

Millions of Europeans choose to buy goods online, but still face many obstacles.
Cross-border parcel delivery prices will soon be more transparent and easier to compare → https://t.co/aZzEG3W2pD #eCommerce https://t.co/YHWS2sm4Qr

The EU-Singapore trade and investment agreements will take EU and Singapore relations to a new level and create more opportunities for EU and Singaporean businesses to grow and create new jobs.
Learn more → https://t.co/9YWxRyPPUe #EUtrade https://t.co/OmrAnUmGnz

The EU-Japan Economic Partnership Agreement will further improve the position of EU exporters and investors on Japan's large market, while including strong guarantees for the protection of EU standards and values. 
Learn more → https://t.co/1lhaXcwxRP #EUTrade https://t.co/wxDMwpw3Ii

Press conference by @jyrkikatainen and @MalmstromEU on the Economic Partnership Agreement between the EU and Japan, and the trade and investment agreements between the EU and Singapore #EUTrade https://t.co/Yj0ikgVAFu

Today is the International Day for Monuments and Sites!
Learn how we preserve the great monuments and sites surrounding us throughout Europe → https://t.co/C3ukg8FQeb  #EuropeforCulture #heritage4generations #ICOMOS https://t.co/pizrCA0YVX

In two weeks, we will present our proposals for a #EUbudget beyond 2020.
The current EU budget represents only about 1% of the wealth generated by the economies of its Member States every year. https://t.co/LX36bmQHRU

Electronic evidence is increasingly important in criminal proceedings.
We are making sure that criminals and terrorists cannot exploit electronic communication technologies to hide their criminal actions and evade justice → https://t.co/iklxJJ7B3T #SecurityUnion https://t.co/EUtZBYtlIz

We propose to improve the security features of EU citizens' identity cards with

📉 gradual phase out of non-compliant cards

We take action to restrict explosives precursors and firearms, step up the security of ID cards, and facilitate access to electronic evidence.
Press conference on #SecurityUnion by @Avramopoulos, @VeraJourova and @JKingEU https://t.co/r7uMNYm2S8

Our enlargement policy continues to be a key engine driving reforms in the Western Balkans. Today, we publish reports on #WesternBalkans partners and Turkey → https://t.co/MORB37i2IT https://t.co/L0HnZui2k1
